{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Crypto registry with 50+ entries, include_str! embedding, HashMap lookup, override support","closed_at":"2026-03-04T01:23:43Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"ed61c3db811b42b43e2989fb60aacedb80db253d87f73f5e20553b3101716d63","created_at":"2026-03-03T15:20:05Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Ship a static config file mapping known crypto function paths that frontends consult during analysis. This is Layer 1 of crypto function recognition (str-mxa3) — zero runtime cost, high precision.\n\nRegistry format: TOML or JSON, organized by language and package. Each entry specifies:\n- Function path (e.g. crypto.createDecipheriv)\n- Direction: encrypt | decrypt | both (for authenticated encryption)\n- Parameter roles: which arg is key, which is data, which is IV/nonce\n- Output semantics: plaintext or ciphertext\n\nInitial coverage:\n- Node.js: crypto module (createDecipheriv, privateDecrypt, subtle.decrypt), crypto-js (CryptoJS.AES.decrypt, CryptoJS.DES.decrypt, etc.), tweetnacl (secretbox.open), libsodium-wrappers\n- Go: crypto/aes + crypto/cipher (NewCBCDecrypter, AEAD.Open/Seal, Stream XORKeyStream), x/crypto (chacha20poly1305, nacl/secretbox)\n- Rust: aes-gcm (Aes256Gcm::decrypt), ring (aead::open_in_place, aead::seal_in_place), chacha20poly1305 crate\n\nFrontends load the registry at startup and match against call targets during analysis/instrumentation. Matched calls get reported to the core engine via the crypto boundary protocol message.\n\nThe registry file lives in a well-known location (e.g. shatter-core/data/crypto-registry.toml) and is extensible by users via a local override file.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-34xq","is_templa