{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":"2026-03-03T19:04:15Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"6668885dca43f1ba43b457dfa211ed56d24ede44094c3356771bb0240f3f0f90","created_at":"2026-03-03T15:52:52Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Both solve_for_new_path and solve_constraints in solver.rs create Config::new() with no params. Z3 crate 0.19 provides Config::set_timeout_msec(ms) — context-level timeout. When Z3 hits deadline, solver.check() returns SatResult::Unknown with reason 'timeout'; check_and_extract already handles this as SolverError::Unknown. Add solver_timeout_ms: Option\u003cu64\u003e param to both solve functions. Apply cfg.set_timeout_msec(ms) when Some. Add solver_timeout_ms to ExploreConfig (explorer.rs) and thread through orchestrator.rs:396. Add --solver-timeout CLI flag (optional, seconds) to Explore/Scan/Run. Add test: 1ms timeout on satisfiable constraint → either Sat or Unknown (no panic).","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-36cd","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"Plan: docs/plans/str-kapl-resilience-timeouts-memory.md section 4","original_size":null,"owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":1,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Z3 solver timeout","updated_at":"2026-03-03T19:04:15Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":"2026-03-04T16:29:47Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"e16d58fc3428e00eeedf407dbb455bdbc71e563fce62e66e2fd59fb911120d31","created_at":"2026-03-04T02:51:28Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"## Problem\n\nWhen multiple shatter processes run concurrently (e.g. make -j4 with per-file explore targets), shared state files in .shatter/ are subject to lost-update races. Atomic writes (temp+rename) prevent corruption but not lost updates — two processes can read pool.json, add entries, and last-rename-wins loses the first process's additions.\n\nAffected files: .shatter/seeds/pool.json, .shatter/batch-state.json, any future shared mutable state.\n\n## Solution\n\nUse the fs2 crate (thin wrapper over flock() syscall) for exclusive locking around read-modify-write operations on shared state files. flock is kernel-managed — locks release automatically on process exit, crash, SIGKILL, or OOM. No stale locks possible, no expiration needed.\n\nPattern:\n```rust\nuse fs2::FileExt;\nlet lock = File::create(\".shatter/pool.lock\")?;\nlock.lock_exclusive()?;\n// read-modify-write pool.json\n// lock released when dropped\n```\n\nFor non-critical paths (e.g. pool update after exploration), use try_lock_exclusive() and skip the update if another process holds the lock — pool updates are best-effort.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. Add fs2 dependency to shatter-core/Cargo.toml\n2. Create a small locking helper in shatter-core (e.g. src/file_lock.rs) wrapping fs2 with .shatter/*.lock convention\n3. Wrap InterestingPool save/load in exclusive lock\n4. Wrap BatchState save/load in exclusive lock\n5. Add integration test verifying concurrent access doesn't lose updates\n\n## Not in scope\n- SQLite migration (separate decision if needed later)\n- Per-file pool splitting (orthogonal optimization)","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-37mm","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Add fs2-based flock locking for .shatter/ shared state files","updated_at":"2026-03-04T16:29:47Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
